@page "/about"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>About - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">About grow.IT</span>
        <h1>Built for founders who know the work, but need help proving it.</h1>
        <p>Grow.IT exists because many mission-led founders are doing real community work without the records, reports, and funding language needed to grow safely.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-grid-section">
        <div class="contact-grid">
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>The Problem</h2>
                <p>Founders are often asked for impact reports, financial history, board structure, service costs, and funding narratives before they have the systems to produce them.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>The Product</h2>
                <p>Grow.IT saves organization data, people served, programs, funding sources, service records, outcomes, documents, and follow-ups in one connected workspace.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>The Outcome</h2>
                <p>The platform helps turn everyday service work into organized data, clearer reporting, ASC readiness, and a professional portfolio founders can use.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>Our product principle</h2>
            <p>Every feature should make the founder's job easier. If a workflow adds confusion, repeats questions, or traps data inside the platform, it does not match the vision.</p>
            <p>Grow.IT is designed to meet founders where they are: they can answer simple questions in their own words, save what they know, and let the system organize it into useful operational proof.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>See how Grow.IT supports your organization.</h2>
            <p>Bring your real operating questions: programs, service costs, reports, donors, board readiness, and funding goals.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?demo=1&subject=Demo%20Request" class="btn btn-primary">Request Demo</a>
                <a href="/docs" class="btn btn-outline">How It Works</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
